  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Acetaminophen is a drug commonly used in palliative care unit, for its antalgic and
      antipyretic effects. Several administration routes are possible but the use of the
      sub-cutaneous route is actually not supported by recommandations.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
